The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Thapar scion takes over as Bilt chief

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, April 25: Thapar family patriarch L.M. Thapar has stepped down as chairman of Ballarpur Industries Limited (Bilt). His nephew, Gautam Thapar, will take over the position.

 L.M. Thapar has announced his retirement as chairman of Bilt. He will take on the role of chairman emeritus. Gautam has been appointed as chairman by the board, a company statement said.

 Both changes will be effective from July 1.

 The company has drawn up a Rs 1200-crore expansion plan and has set a turnover target of Rs 4000 crore over the next four years. The programme involves expanding its production capacity of paper and pulp to 1 million tonnes by 2010.

 Meanwhile, the company has announced its results for the nine months ended March 31. The company follows a financial year from July 1 to June 30.

 Consolidated profit after tax grew by 15.71 per cent to Rs 147.69 crore from Rs 127.64 crore. 

 Consolidated paper revenues grew by 10.30 per cent to Rs 1,318.90 crore from Rs 1,195.72 crore.

 Bilt is a leading manufacturer of writing and printing paper with a market share of 20 per cent. 

 It also has approximately 60 per cent share in the coated paper market.

 The company sold 3,07,044 mt paper compared with 2,87,597 mt in the corresponding period of the previous year.




